We further expanded the application of O-CDs as photovoltaic materials. On the one hand, O-CDs/starch solid fluorescent powders were prepared and their optical properties were investigated by solid-state fluorescence spectroscopy (Fig. 7
                        ). As shown in Fig. S16, the emission spectrum of the fluorescent powder was similar to that of the O-CDs solution. On the other hand, O-CDs/PVA fluorescent flexible films were prepared (Fig. 8
                        ). When O-CDs were not added, the flexible films showed weak blue fluorescence. With the introduction of O-CDs, the orange luminescence of the flexible films was gradually enhanced, which was consistent with the results of solid-state fluorescence spectroscopy (Fig. S17).
